 {\"sentence\": \"In 17 playoff games, Nembhard averaged 14.9 points, 5.5 assists and 3.3 rebounds while shooting 56.0% from the field and 48.3% from downtown.\", \"from\": 3282, \"to\": 3423, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RUI HACHIMURA, JAPAN  Hachimura headlined Team Japan\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 16-man roster that was announced in late June, as the 6-foot-8 forward is likely to represent his home country in back-to-back Olympic Games.\\u00c2  While it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a historic journey (Japan hasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t qualified in men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s basketball in back-to-back Games since 1972 and 1976), Japan doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t want to relive the experiences from the 2020 Games, in which it went 0-3 and finished 11th out of 12th in the final standings as the host country.\", \"from\": 3425, \"to\": 3912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3425, \"end\": 3438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RUI HACHIMURA\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\"}, {\"begin\": 3447, \"end\": 3456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hachimura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\"}, {\"begin\": 3659, \"end\": 3664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5576055668607591, \"rank\": 0.7932566398899095, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3750, \"end\": 3755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource